hits.name: Bordeaux Rouge
hits.description: An intense, ruby red colour with purple highlights. The wine has a rich, open nose with attractive aromas of red berry fruit (raspberry, cherry) and strawberry jam accompanied by a touch of menthol. Round and full on the palate, it displays fine balance with an elegant tannic structure and a pleasant range of crisp, fruity flavours enhanced by a touch of liquorice.

hits.name: Réserve Graves Rouge
hits.description: Reserve Mouton Graves red fully expresses the distinctive characteristics of its appellation. A blend of 55% Cabernet Sauvignon, 30% Merlot and 15% Cabernet Franc, it reveals all the refinement and charm of its terrior.

hits.description: Intense purple with a slightly carmine tint. The nose opens on ripe black fruit aromas, especially bilberry and black cherry. Mocha notes come through with airing. Together with soft spice such as cumin and paprika, through red and black fruit aromas still predominate. The palate is both opulent and precise with nicely forward fruit, while the dense mid-palate reveals powerful and well-rounded tannins. The finish shows attractive length on rip fruit and spice flavors.
